7\u20132008\n| clubs10        = [[CE Manresa|Manresa]]\n| caps10         = 17\n| goals10        = 0\n| years11        = 2008\u20132010\n| clubs11        = [[CF Balaguer|Balaguer]]\n| caps11         = 51\n| goals11        = 7\n| years12        = 2010\u20132013\n| clubs12        = [[FC Andorra]]\n| caps12         = \n| goals12        = \n| years13        = 2013\u20132016\n| clubs13        = [[FC Santa Coloma]]\n| caps13         = 50\n| goals13        = 19\n| years14        = 2016\u2013\n| clubs14        = [[FC Andorra]]\n| caps14         = 21\n| goals14        = 3\n| nationalyears1 = 2000\u2013\n| nationalteam1  = [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 84\n| nationalgoals1 = 2\n| ntupdate       = 14 May 2017\n| pcupdate       = 10 October 2017\n}}\n'''Marc Pujol Pons''' (born 21 August 1982)<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/players/marc-pujol/55897/ Soccerway profile]</ref> is an [[Andorra]]n [[Association football|footballer]]. He currently plays for [[FC Santa Coloma]] in [[Andorra]]'s [[Primera Divisi\u00f3]] and the [[Andorra national football team|Andorran national team]]. Pujol has scored 2 goals for the [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] in competitive fixtures.\nPlayed in the [[Intertoto|UEFA Intertoto Cup]] for [[UE Sant Juli\u00e0]] against [[Lausanne Sports|FC Lausanne-Sports]] ([[2001 UEFA Intertoto Cup|2001]]) and [[Coleraine F.C.|Coleraine FC]] ([[2002 UEFA Intertoto Cup|2002]]) - 4 matches and 0 goals.\n\nAchievements:\n1. Third Place at [[Preferent Territorial de Catalunya|Primera Catalana]] 2000/01 and promotion to [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|Tercera division]] with [[FC Andorra|Andorra]].\n2. 3rd Place at [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|Tercera division]] group 5 2002/03 with [[UE Sant Andreu|Sant Andreu]].\n3. Winner of [[Andorran Supercup]] 2003 with [[UE Sant Juli\u00e0]].<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/ando03.html Andorra 2003/04 (RSSSF)]</ref>\n4. 2nd Place at Tercera Catalana 2010/11 and promoted to Segona Catalana with [[FC Andorra|Andorra]].\n5. 2nd Place at Segona Catalana 2011/12 and promoted to [[Preferent Territorial de Catalunya|Primera Catalana]] with [[FC Andorra|Andorra]].\n6. Winner of [[Andorra]]'s [[Primera Divisi\u00f3]] 2013/14 with [[FC Santa Coloma]].\n\n==International==\n\nPujol played in a match against England at Old Trafford but had to withdraw due to a leg injury after a tangle with [[Ashley Cole]].<ref>http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2008/matches/round=2241/match=83917/postmatch/report/index.html#england+ease+winning+start</ref>\n\n==National team statistics==\n<ref>[http://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=17131 eu-football profile]</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! colspan=3 | [[Andorra national football team|Andorra national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|-\n|2000||4||0\n|-\n|2001||1||0\n|-\n|2002||4||0\n|-\n|2003||5||0\n|-\n|2004||5||1\n|-\n|2005||5||0\n|-\n|2006||5||0\n|-\n|2007||5||0\n|-\n|2008||5||1\n|-\n|2009||4||0\n|-\n|2010||5||0\n|-\n|2011||3||0\n|-\n|2012||6||0\n|-\n|2013||4||0\n|-\n|2014||4||0\n|-\n|2015||1||0\n|-\n|2016||2||0\n|-\n!Total||68||2\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Andorra's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"soccerway 2\">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/marc-pujol/55897/|title=Andorra \u2013 Marc Pujol \u2013 Profile with news, career statistics and history|publisher=soccerway.com|accessdate=September 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!Goal!!Date!!Venue!!Opponent!!Score!!Result!!Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 8 September 2004 || [[Estadi Comunal d'Andorra la Vella]], [[Andorra la Vella]], Andorra || {{fb|ROM}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20133 || align=center | 1\u20135 || [[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group 1|2006 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 2. || 10 September 2008 || Estadi Comunal d'Andorra la Vella, Andorra la Vella, Andorra || {{fb|BLR}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20131 || align=center | 1\u20133 