ll team|Andorran national team]]. Pujol has scored 2 goals for the [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] in competitive fixtures.\nPlayed in the [[Intertoto|UEFA Intertoto Cup]] for [[UE Sant Juli\u00e0]] against [[Lausanne Sports|FC Lausanne-Sports]] ([[2001 UEFA Intertoto Cup|2001]]) and [[Coleraine F.C.|Coleraine FC]] ([[2002 UEFA Intertoto Cup|2002]]) - 4 matches and 0 goals.\n\nAchievements:\n1. Third Place at [[Preferent Territorial de Catalunya|Primera Catalana]] 2000/01 and promotion to [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|Tercera division]] with [[FC Andorra|Andorra]].\n2. 3rd Place at [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|Tercera division]] group 5 2002/03 with [[UE Sant Andreu|Sant Andreu]].\n3. Winner of [[Andorran Supercup]] 2003 with [[UE Sant Juli\u00e0]].<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/ando03.html Andorra 2003/04 (RSSSF)]</ref>\n4. 2nd Place at Tercera Catalana 2010/11 and promoted to Segona Catalana with [[FC Andorra|Andorra]].\n5. 2nd Place at Segona Catalana 2011/12 and promoted to [[Preferent Territorial de Catalunya|Primera Catalana]] with [[FC Andorra|Andorra]].\n6. Winner of [[Andorra]]'s [[Primera Divisi\u00f3]] 2013/14 with [[FC Santa Coloma]].\n\n==International==\n\nPujol played in a match against England at Old Trafford but had to withdraw due to a leg injury after a tangle with [[Ashley Cole]].<ref>http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2008/matches/round=2241/match=83917/postmatch/report/index.html#england+ease+winning+start</ref>\n\n==National team statistics==\n<ref>[http://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=17131 eu-football profile]</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! colspan=3 | [[Andorra national football team|Andorra national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|-\n|2000||4||0\n|-\n|2001||1||0\n|-\n|2002||4||0\n|-\n|2003||5||0\n|-\n|2004||5||1\n|-\n|2005||5||0\n|-\n|2006||5||0\n|-\n|2007||5||0\n|-\n|2008||5||1\n|-\n|2009||4||0\n|-\n|2010||5||0\n|-\n|2011||3||0\n|-\n|2012||6||0\n|-\n|2013||4||0\n|-\n|2014||4||0\n|-\n|2015||1||0\n|